♪Don't be afraid of the long journey♪

2
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:34,740
♪Love will comfort your missing♪

3
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:38,620
♪All the wounds will scab over♪

4
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:41,980
♪And turn into the blossoms of time♪

5
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:48,700
♪Someone will wipe them away for you♪

6
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,580
♪Don't feel lonely, moving on♪

7
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:56,420
♪Share your story with time♪

8
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:03,100
♪It will respond
with a gentle beam of light♪

9
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,820
♪Wishing you find her in the crowd♪

10
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,220
♪And rest content with a simple life♪

11
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:16,660
♪Even though life is full of regrets♪

12
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,180
♪May you always maintain enthusiasm♪

13
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,540
♪For every winter and summer♪

14
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,980
[Love Is Panacea]
[Episode 10]

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:26,960
[The show is the Major Project
for Supporting Literature and Art]

16
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,980
[in Sichuan Province in 2022]

17
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[Based on the novel "Healer"
by Ningmeng Yuyan]

18
00:01:32,340 --> 00:01:32,980
Slowly.

19
00:01:37,620 --> 00:01:38,500
Slow down, Fang Mingfan.

20
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:39,220
It's a mountain road.

21
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:40,540
Are you scared?

22
00:01:41,660 --> 00:01:42,660
No, I'm not.

23
00:01:46,180 --> 00:01:47,300
You had to come.

24
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:52,620
What if something happens to us?

25
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:54,620
How are we going to save them two?

26
00:01:56,980 --> 00:01:58,540
With this speed...

27
00:01:58,740 --> 00:01:59,420
Careful.

28
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:02,620
We can hardly get there by daybreak.

29
00:02:04,660 --> 00:02:05,660
What now?

30
00:02:06,180 --> 00:02:07,860
Their phones must be dead.

31
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:11,860
I just called them,
but I couldn't get through.

32
00:02:14,420 --> 00:02:15,060
This won't do.

33
00:02:16,540 --> 00:02:17,980
Boss never gives up on me.

34
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:19,980
I can never leave him alone.

35
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:21,540
What do you mean to give up on you?

36
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:22,620
Why should he do that?

37
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:25,420
Didn't you ask me

38
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:27,180
about my operative mortality?

39
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,420
I said that I had no record.

40
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:35,300
Actually, in my first operation,

41
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:39,980
my patient died on the operating table.

42
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:43,540
That night,

43
00:02:46,620 --> 00:02:47,580
the patient's vitals were unstable.

44
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:48,980
Blood pressure 82, 48.

45
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:49,980
Blood oxygen 70.

46
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,420
This is a blood blister-like aneurysm.

47
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:55,300
The hemorrhagic spots
must be taken care of now.

48
00:02:55,780 --> 00:02:57,540
How long before Dr. He arrives?

49
00:02:57,540 --> 00:02:58,740
Dr. He is still having the runs.

50
00:02:58,820 --> 00:03:00,100
Director Zhang is in an operation now.

51
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:02,340
Blood oxygen is lower than 60 now.

52
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:03,820
Bleeding is over 1,000ml.

53
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:05,660
We can't wait.

54
00:03:05,660 --> 00:03:06,660
Do the operation now.

55
00:03:06,980 --> 00:03:07,780
Dr. He only told you

56
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:08,980
to maintain the patient's vitals.

57
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:10,100
If you do it now,

58
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:11,700
you'll be responsible for the result.

59
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,420
Blood blister-like aneurysms

60
00:03:13,940 --> 00:03:15,500
are the most difficult and riskiest.

61
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:16,460
Can you do it?

62
00:03:17,420 --> 00:03:18,460
If I don't try,

63
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:20,460
he'll be dead for sure.

64
00:03:21,620 --> 00:03:22,340
The operation begins now.

65
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:23,580
Gelatin sponge.

66
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:32,660
The patient is in shock.
He needs a transfusion now.

67
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:35,700
The patient's having a cardiac arrest.

68
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:36,940
Give him CPR now.

69
00:03:58,060 --> 00:03:59,420
Dr. He didn't show up.

70
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:00,220
The patient was dying.

71
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:01,180
What else can I do?

72
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:02,940
Watch him die?

73
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:05,020
You've only been an assistant before.

74
00:04:05,020 --> 00:04:06,460
You have never dealt with aneurysms.

75
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:07,940
How can you act without permission?

76
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:10,300
Thankfully, his family are sensible
and won't hold you accountable.

77
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:12,940
Go reflect on yourself properly.

78
00:04:16,540 --> 00:04:18,620
He can't even handle aneurysms,

79
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:20,340
but he dared to act
without the attending doctor.

80
00:04:20,340 --> 00:04:21,620
Who does he think he is?

81
00:04:21,740 --> 00:04:22,700
Dr. He said

82
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,340
that someone
isn't meant to be a surgeon.

83
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:25,980
I think no medical teams

84
00:04:25,980 --> 00:04:27,620
